21. Cloud Service Types

Cloud services are mainly of 3 types:

🖥️ 1. IaaS (Infrastructure as a Service)

👉 You get basic infrastructure like servers, storage, networking
✔ You manage everything else (OS, apps)

💡 Example:

AWS EC2
Azure Virtual Machines

👉 Simple meaning: “Rent a computer in the cloud”

🧱 2. PaaS (Platform as a Service)

👉 You get a ready platform to build apps
✔ Provider manages servers + OS
✔ You focus only on code

💡 Example:

Google App Engine
Azure App Service

👉 Simple meaning: “Just deploy your code, no server worries”

📱 3. SaaS (Software as a Service)

👉 Fully ready software used via internet
✔ No setup needed

💡 Example:

Gmail
Google Drive
Netflix

👉 Simple meaning: “Use software directly”

🧠 Quick comparison
Type	You manage	Provider manages
IaaS	Apps, OS	Servers, network
PaaS	Only code	Everything else
SaaS	Nothing	Everything
⚡ 22. Serverless

👉 Serverless means you don’t manage servers at all — cloud runs your code automatically.

✔ You just upload functions/code
✔ It runs only when needed
✔ You pay only when it runs

💡 Example:

AWS Lambda
Azure Functions
🧠 Simple meaning

“No server management, just write code and run”

⚡ Difference from normal cloud
Traditional	Serverless
Always running server	Runs only when needed
Pay always	Pay per use
You manage servers	Provider manages everything
🎯 Final summary
IaaS = rent infrastructure
PaaS = build apps easily
SaaS = use ready apps
Serverless = run code without managing servers
